 style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="http://www.bishop-hill.net/blog/2012/11/25/28-gate-still-running.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.bishop-hill.net/blog/2012/11/25/28-gate-still-running.html</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">4.3 Actually, not a lot. Even when nailed. The irony is how those involved in this have subsequently foundered, but not on the basis of s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">uch activities, or in a timely manner. And then there’s the utterly bizarre Wild West of the BBC staff twitter accounts:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="http://biasedbbc.org/in-their-own-tweets/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://biasedbbc.org/in-their-own-tweets/</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">'I present The Newsroom on the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">BBC World Service. Not a BBC spokeswoman. Occasionally facetious. And, sigh, RT doesn't = endorsement.'</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">One just from the other day. In her bio she says she presents stuff on the BBC, but is not a BBC spokeswoman. No other organisation would get away with</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt"> this